<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>SPECIAL CREDIT OPPORTUNITIES  In addition to the accredited courses listed in the academic catalog in the section Curricula and Courses, Quincy University will accept a combined total of 40 semester hours of credit from nontraditional sources including the:
ADVANCED PLACEMENT PROGRAM (AP)
The University participates in the Advanced Placement Program and grants credit for courses in which grades of 4 or 5 have been earned. A grade of 3 is acceptable in some cases. The credit granted varies by department or discipline by score achieved; students should inquire of the Office of the Registrar concerning the application of scores to credit hours by subject matter.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.quincy.edu/resources/academics/academiccatalog2012_2013.pdf" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

